s provide detailed critical analysis of films by Dominique Cabrera, Laetitia Masson, Noémie Lvovsky and Marion Vernoux, and present common thread including the possible construction of social intimacy, the political demystification of romance narratives and the role of nostalgia, to argue that their work uses popular genres in order to challenge dominant cultural representation that resonates beyond the immediate parameters of contemporary French cinema. This book will be of interest to researchers working in French and European cinema, to students of Film Studies and French and Francophone Studies, and to film enthusiasts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuteur theory (Motion pictures). 0aMotion picture producers and directorszFrance. 0aMotion pictureszFrancexHistory. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aDominique Cabrera.  aFrance.  aLaetitia Masson.  aMarion Vernoux.  aNoémie Lvovsky.  aacademic film criticism.  adetective narratives.  afilm directors.  agendered creative identity.  aromantic comedy.1 aDobson, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614170540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141705423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141705/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles